"Galen":http://galenframework.com is a test framework originally designed for testing layout of web applications but is also a great tool for functional testing. When it comes to testing a responsive layout it works in a following way:
# Open a page in browser
# Resize it to specified size
# Test the layout according to user-defined specs

It uses "Selenium":http://www.seleniumhq.org/ for interacting with elements on page and getting their locations and dimensions. 
Once it sees that something is wrong - Galen reports the error, makes a screenshot and highlights the misbehaving element on it.

